<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1439,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="MCZ" collectorName="Mr. Beyer. The" location="California" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="California" typeStatus="syntype">
Fall described 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fall" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[370,537,1476,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Lichenophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciculatus">
<emphasis box="[370,537,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">L. fasciculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a specimen from southern 
<collectingRegion box="[967,1081,1476,1502]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">California</collectingRegion>
(Santa Rosa) collected by 
<collectorName pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Mr. Beyer. The</collectorName>
<typeStatus box="[285,372,1513,1539]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">syntype</typeStatus>
is in Harvard University collection, and very good-quality photographs of the specimen and labels can be found on the website of the 
<collectionCode box="[615,679,1548,1574]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" name="Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" type="Museum">MCZ</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1439,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
Due to characteristic, very long and erect pubescence on the body (which is not found in any other species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lesne" authorityYear="1899" box="[193,363,1620,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Lichenophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[193,363,1620,1646]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Lichenophanes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus), it cannot be doubted that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fall" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[744,908,1620,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Lichenophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciculatus">
<emphasis box="[744,908,1620,1646]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">L. fasciculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identical with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lesne" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1102,1263,1620,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Lichenophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penicillatus">
<emphasis box="[1102,1263,1620,1646]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">L. penicillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter was described slightly earlier from 
<collectingCountry box="[505,591,1656,1682]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(MNHN). So 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fall" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[759,925,1656,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Lichenophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciculatus">
<emphasis box="[759,925,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">L. fasciculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lesne" baseAuthorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Bostrichidae" genus="Lichenophanes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penicillatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">L. penicillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Full synonymy of the species is as follows:
</paragraph>
